1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:05,850
Now, the validations that we have right now are server side.

2
00:00:05,850 --> 00:00:12,090
And what I mean by that is you will notice when we hit the create button, it hits our debugging point

3
00:00:12,090 --> 00:00:16,230
in the controller and then it returns back the error message.

4
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:19,470
You will notice the page also reloads.

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,330
There we go.

6
00:00:20,340 --> 00:00:22,400
You can see the spinner at the top.

7
00:00:22,410 --> 00:00:24,990
That means it is going to the server.

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:30,860
But what if we want to implement client side validation using JavaScript?

9
00:00:30,870 --> 00:00:38,010
We can easily do validations in the browser itself to make sure this field is populated or not.

10
00:00:38,730 --> 00:00:43,200
Dot net core has already provided some of those things built in.

11
00:00:43,530 --> 00:00:49,600
If we take a look at validation scripts partial, it has the validation jQuery.

12
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:53,280
Using that we can do client side validation.

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:01,170
And for that we do not have to write much code inside the create view where we have the validation for

14
00:01:01,170 --> 00:01:05,220
we have to include reference to this partial view.

15
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:12,210
So basically we have to add this partial view, which is a shared view inside the main create view.

16
00:01:12,210 --> 00:01:20,040
And that way whatever code is inside the shared will also be added to the create view that we have.

17
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:23,970
Now how can we add or consume a partial view?

18
00:01:24,850 --> 00:01:26,260
That is pretty simple.

19
00:01:26,380 --> 00:01:33,760
Since this partial view is only having the scripts, we will have to add that in a new section here

20
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,590
for scripts.

21
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:38,750
And I have some space.

22
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,130
Let me remove that.

23
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:43,520
Inside there we will have the razor syntax.

24
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:50,170
And when we have to consume any partial view, we can do that with the partial tag.

25
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,700
And there we have to provide name.

26
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,330
Make sure to copy the name.

27
00:01:55,330 --> 00:01:59,980
It must exactly match the name that we have in validation scripts.

28
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:00,850
Partial.

29
00:02:00,970 --> 00:02:03,520
It should be the exact file name.

30
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:07,000
If that is not same, it will not work.

31
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:14,340
And with that it has added that partial view in the script section for the View page.

32
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:19,990
Now, because this partial view was script related, we added that in the script.

33
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:25,770
But if this was not a script related, you can directly add that right here.

34
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:30,480
When we have to consume some partial view in a master page.

35
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:33,580
But that is not the case for now.

36
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:38,440
So we will add that inside the script section that we have.

37
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:46,970
But here you have noticed how we can consume a partial view with the partial tag helper that we have

38
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,540
in the.

39
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:48,890
.Net framework.

40
00:02:49,890 --> 00:02:56,400
And where we have the name here, by default, it will go and look into the shared folder because that

41
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,700
is the default location for any partial view.

42
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:07,450
Because of that, it will automatically find that and it will add the JavaScript that are needed for

43
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:09,400
client side validation.

44
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:11,170
Simple as that.

45
00:03:12,290 --> 00:03:14,930
With that, let me restart the application.

46
00:03:14,930 --> 00:03:21,950
And now the validation will be first done on client side and for custom validation it will go to the

47
00:03:21,950 --> 00:03:23,030
server side.

48
00:03:23,450 --> 00:03:32,270
So in order to test that, actually let me go back and uncomment these lines here because they are custom

49
00:03:32,270 --> 00:03:35,570
validation and let me run the project.

50
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:45,090
So if we go to category here, and if we create a new category this time when we hit create.

51
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,820
Let me also add a debugging point.

52
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:50,880
You will notice it will not go to the server.

53
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,930
There will not be any spinner.

54
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:58,590
We see the error message and you can see it is not hitting our breakpoint as well.

55
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:05,240
If I enter the category name test here create, we have the other validation.

56
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:12,990
Once we fulfill that, if it is more than 100, you can see when I am typing it automatically displays

57
00:04:12,990 --> 00:04:14,160
the validation.

58
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:22,079
But the custom validation that we have is category name and display order cannot be same is on server

59
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:26,400
side and client side validation is not aware of that.

60
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:35,010
So when we hit create button this time it will hit our breakpoint and it goes to the server and displays

61
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:37,140
the server side validation.

62
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:46,540
With that, we have seen how easy it is to add client side validation in our views in the .net project.

63
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:55,000
We just have to add the scripts that are provided by default on the page where we want client side validation.

